Former Edo Senator, Dr. Domingo Alaba Obende has joined the race to emerge as the National Secretary of Nigeria’s ruling party, the All Progressives Congress, at the national convention slated for the 26th of February. The UNIBEN and University of East London Business School alumnus represented Edo North Senatorial District in the 7th Senate and remains one of the foundational members of the APC, having belonged to one of its merger parties, the Action Congress of Nigeria. His manifesto document expresses his intention to change the narrative of party leadership and establish a bottom-top structure for sustained, collective growth of the APC. He will be counting on his extensive network within the party and reputation as a trusted party leader and team By Ehigimetor Igbauba Benin - A former senator from Edo North Senatorial district, Mr Domingo Obende, has said that the victory of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in the Sept. 28 governorship election was a testimony by Edo people that they love good things. Obende, a member of the senate… In "Politics" ABUJA (Sundiata Post) - The All Progressives Congress (APC) has warned against the declaring any result from the Anambra Central Senatorial primary election conducted by the party. [pro_ad_display_adzone id="70560"] A statement issued on Thursday in Abuja by Mai Mala Buni, national secretary of the party, said "Senator Domingo Obende who was… In "Politics" •Oshiomhole ABUJA - Efforts to get the embattled national chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Comrade Adams Oshiomhole out at all cost has continued with the resolution of South South leaders to replace him with Victor Giadom even in acting capacity. They also insisted that the party’s National Executive… In "Politics"